Instead, vehicles will be diverted to 99 Ave to access Bellamy Hill Road where a new traffic light has been added. I will miss my shortcut from Connors Road via Low Level Bridge towards 109 Street as this was actually faster than using the James Macdonald Bridge turn off due to multiple traffic light phases along 98 Ave, but I do understand that this intersection may be overwhelming to some drivers.

description: Galápagos penguins are endangered, with an estimate of fewer than 2,000 individuals remaining. A new study using model predictions has uncovered a likely rapid accumulation of microplastics across the food web, with the most microplastics building up in the endangered penguins, then moving down the food web to barracuda, anchovies, sardines, herrings, black-striped salema, and zooplankton. “The goal of this food web bioaccumulation modeling work was to provide science and data to support risk management of hazardous plastic waste, reduce microplastic emissions in the oceans and marine remote UNESCO Heritage sites such as the Galápagos Islands, and inform local and international marine policy to conserve endangered, endemic seabird species of Galápagos Marine Reserve,” Juan Jose Alava, senior author of the study and principal investigator of the Ocean Pollution Research Unit at the University of British Columbia’s Institute for the Oceans and Fisheries Full article below https://www.ecowatch.com/microplastics-galapagos-penguins.html

description: The Kampala Flyover Road Project is a road-improvement initiative in the Central Division of Kampala, the capital city of Uganda. Here are the key details: Objective: The project aims to decongest the city by separating through-traffic from city-street traffic. It focuses on traffic entering the city, mainly from Entebbe along the old Kampala-Entebbe Road and from Mpigi along the Kampala-Mpigi Expressway. Construction: The project involves constructing flyovers at the “Clock Tower” and “Kitgum House,” widening Nsambya Road and Mukwano Road, and improving interfacing roads and junctions. The project stretches over approximately 3.5 kilometers (2 miles). Funding: The Ugandan government, with financing from the Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA), funds the project. Progress: Despite challenges posed by the COVID-19 outbreak, construction is progressing steadily. Excavation works on the 4-lane underpass are nearing completion, and screw piles for the flyover and pedestrian bridges have been delivered on-site12. This project aims to enhance urban transportation, reduce travel times, and alleviate traffic congestion in Kampala. 🚗 #ugandanstiktok #kampalaflyover

description: Ever wondered how some people can seemingly defy the laws of nature by dipping their hands into boiling oil without getting burned? Meet the Leidenfrost effect – a remarkable physical phenomenon where a protective vapor layer is formed due to intense heat, momentarily insulating the skin from the scorching temperature. This fleeting barrier is created when the moisture on the skin instantly vaporizes upon contact with the hot oil. While this might look like a superhuman feat, it’s a dangerous and fleeting trick relying more on physics than on fearlessness. Remember, don’t try this at home – understanding the science is cool, but safety always comes first! #leidenfrosteffect #medical #culinary #science #viral

description: Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez paid tribute to the late #Pose Actress Cecilia Gentili. Cecilia Gentili, an Argentina-born artist and activist known for her work in the immigrant and transgender rights movements in New York City, is being widely remembered following her death last week. She was 52. As an actress, Gentili stood out with her memorable portrayal of Ms. Orlando on the groundbreaking series Pose, which illuminated the experiences of trans women of colour during the AIDS crisis of the 1980s. News of her death broke on Tuesday (February 6), when close friends and family took to her Instagram page to announce her passing, saying: “Our beloved Cecilia Gentili passed away this morning to continue watching over us in spirit. Please be gentle with each other and love one another with ferocity.” Gentili was seen by many as a symbol of hope and resilience. Her journey from Argentina to the bustling streets of New York City was marked by her continuing unwavering advocacy for marginalised communities, from undocumented immigrants to sex workers. She took pivotal roles at prominent organisations like New York City–based AIDS non-profit GMHC and founded Trans Equity Consulting, where her mission was to amplify the voices of marginalised communities. Her activism also took the form of initiatives like Transmissions Fest, a music festival aimed at putting transgender voices centre stage, and fundraising event Fierce Futures in support of Black trans people. Tributes to Cecilia poured in across social media from a range of people from all walks of life. American writer and book editor Raquel Willis said: “Cecilia Gentili was a living legend. A titan, an unapologetic example of trans joy and power. Her spirit lives on in all whom she touched and all she built for us. Rest powerfully and peacefully, Mami. And go kiki with the ancestors. You deserve eternal pleasure.” All of the tributes made one thing very clear: that Cecilia Gentili’s impact had transcended boundaries and will linger for decades to come. #ceciliagentili #trans #lgbt #aoc #uspolitics

description: It's no secret some San Francisco businesses have been hit hard by rampant theft and shoplifting. Safeway has installed gates inside some of their high-theft San Francisco stores where customers have to scan their receipts to exit. At least two San Francisco Safeway stores have the new sliding gates, including this one on Webster Street and the Mission Street store in the Excelsior District. A Safeway spokeswoman wrote in a statement to KPIX 5, "recent changes were made at select Safeway stores in the Bay Area... given the increasing amount of theft. Those updates include operational changes to the front end of the stores to deter shoplifting." Safeway has tried many security measures in recent years, including metal gates to prevent people from leaving through closed registers and long metal poles attached to shopping carts so people can't just run out with a cart full of products. #sanfrancisco #sf #bayarea #california #safeway #shopping #store #groceries #news

description: Ledakan dahsyat yang terjadi di pelabuhan Beirut (Port of Beirut) pada Selasa (4/8/2020) lalu nyatanya sudah diprediksi oleh pihak terkait di Lebanon. Menurut dokumen yang dilihat oleh Reuters dan sumber keamanan senior, pejabat keamanan Lebanon sudah memperingatkan perdana menteri dan presiden bulan lalu. Laporan Direktorat Jenderal Keamanan Negara tentang peristiwa yang mengarah ke ledakan termasuk referensi, dikirim melalui surat pribadi kepada Presiden Michel Aoun dan Perdana Menteri Hassan Diab pada 20 Juli. Mereka mengatakan 2.750 ton amonium nitrat yang disimpan di gudang pelabuhan Beirut menimbulkan risiko keamanan dan dapat menghancurkan ibu kota jika meledak. Lebih dari dua minggu kemudian, bahan kimia industri meledak dalam ledakan besar yang melenyapkan sebagian besar pelabuhan. Tragedi itu menewaskan sedikitnya 163 orang, melukai 6.000 lainnya, dan menghancurkan sekitar 6.000 bangunan.  #fypシ #faktadunia  #foryoupage #information #infoduniaunik1 #info #fyp

description: Over two dozen Lebanon County residents packed a county commissioners meeting last Thursday to show their frustration over the county removing their only ballot drop box. The county is expecting 16,000 voters to vote by mail in the upcoming presidential election with 4,500 of those voters expected to use the drop box that used to be located at the county courthouse. Due to pushback from the community, the commissioners proposed building a shed near the original drop box and staff it with election workers so voters can drive by and drop off their ballot. description: Extremely rare white African wild dog puppy 4 Rivers is currently home to an extraordinary pack of wild dogs with a very leucistic pup. Local researchers have confirmed that this is extremely rare and virtually unheard of in Botswana for the past 30 years or so 🐾 In the 1990s, guides first spotted leucistic puppies in the Kwando area. The males of Kwando's pack have dispersed. These men, identified by photos, established a group dubbed the Golden Pack in the Vumbura area. Some descendants of this golden pack started another family in Kwara, where leucism was still evident but somewhat diluted. Leucism tends to be a lack of melanin in the skin, feathers, or hair. Melanin is the natural pigment responsible for most brown and black coloring. It is mostly genetic and varies in degree, going all the way to pure white in rare cases (like this one at 4 Rivers) or like in the "golden" Vumbura dogs, which are a pale tan tone. Currently, the pup interacts normally with its siblings and adult painted wolves (as African wild dogs are also known). Although this little one is anything but painted! If anything, it's dominant in the hierarchy when it comes to receiving food from adults! This pup may darken as he ages, and there is an outward chance that his whole body will be a large white spot, which sometimes happens with domestic dogs and cats. We'll keep a close eye to see how its color evolves 🐶 Thanks to the expert researchers in Botswana for their insight! Dr Peter Apps Dr John Tico McNutt Dr Gabriele Cozzi Botswana Predator Conservation

description: Thank you Dr Berthrude Albert for bringing this back to our attention  @Dr. Bertrhude Albert . On Feb. 10, 2010 President Bill Clinton, then the UN Special Envoy to Haiti, publicly apologized for forcing Haiti to drop tariffs on imported, subsidized US rice during his time in office.  The policy wiped out Haitian rice farming and seriously damaged Haiti’s ability to be self-sufficient. [ Transcript ] “Since 1981, the United States has followed a policy, until the last year or so when we started rethinking it, that we rich countries that produce a lot of food should sell it to poor countries and relieve them of the burden of producing their own food, so, thank goodness, they can leap directly into the industrial era. It has not worked. It may have been good for some of my farmers in Arkansas, but it has not worked. It was a mistake. It was a mistake that I was a party to. I am not pointing the finger at anybody. I did that. I have to live every day with the consequences of the lost capacity to produce a rice crop in Haiti to feed those people, because of what I did. Nobody else.”

description: Another air hostess of Pakistan International Airlines (PIA) allegedly went missing while on duty in Canada. Sources privy to the matter said that upon investigation, a note expressing gratitude to PIA was discovered alongside her hanging uniform in her room which read out "Thank you, PIA." This marks the third reported case this year of PIA flight attendants allegedly 'slipping' while on duty, with two of them being women. description: OXON HILL, Md. — A 14-year-old middle school girl has been arrested and charged for arranging an attack on a Prince George's County school bus that nearly turned deadly, testimony in the teen's detention hearing Monday revealed. On May 1, three teen boys pushed their way past a Prince George’s County school bus driver and aide in Oxon Hill and tried to shoot a middle school student in the head, but the gun misfired. Video of the attack shows a teenaged attacker holding a gun to the victim’s head and chest while his two accomplices hold the victim down. All three teens then beat the victim and fled.  Now, a 14-year-old girl is accused of planning the "hit-squad" attack. The eighth-grader is accused of texting the boys moments before the attack to let them know the victim was on the bus.  The teen girl was arrested over the weekend. Though her family begged for her to be released into home detention before her trial, she was ordered held without bail at a juvenile facility during a court hearing Monday. Prosecutors told the judge a gang rivalry was involved in the attack. The victim's mother also asked the judge not to let the girl go home, saying she, her son and the school bus driver feared she could orchestrate another attack if released. “She planned this out, and she set it up to a T," the victim’s mother said in court.  #fypシ゚viral  #blackmedia

description: The Supreme Court on Monday restored Donald Trump to 2024 presidential primary ballots, rejecting state attempts to hold the Republican former president accountable for the Capitol riot. The justices ruled a day before the Super Tuesday primaries that states cannot invoke a post-Civil War constitutional provision to keep presidential candidates from appearing on ballots. That power resides with Congress, the court wrote in an unsigned opinion. The outcome ends efforts in Colorado, Illinois, Maine and elsewhere to kick Trump, the front-runner for his party's nomination, off the ballot because of his attempts to undo his loss in the 2020 election to Democrat Joe Biden, culminating in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the Capitol. description: 🌝 In the Arctic Circle,between Russia and Canada, it only lasts a few seconds, but it's worth seeing. It's a spectacular sight - and in real time!Imagine that you are in a place between Canada and Russia and that, suddenly and for just 30 seconds, the moon appears in all its splendor and disappears before your eyes. Looks like the moon is going to collide with the earth.But even more impressive, and for just 5 seconds, a total eclipse of the sun takes place right after. It's unprecedented and spectacular! The video was shot in real time. This phenomenon happens at the perigee point of a star's orbit around the Earth, where the proximity of the Moon is so evident that, suddenly, we realize the great speed at which the Earth is moving. 🌎🌕🌚 #Moon #russia #phenomenon #ArcticCircle #canada​ #real​ ©️KevinPietersen

description: Boston Dynamics’ Robot Atlas shows off human-like skills. The Atlas robot can now run, jump, pick up, throw heavy objects and perform complex moves that may one day help humans in factories or on construction sites.  The video released titled “Atlas Gets a Grip” displays the Atlas robot picking up not only the tool bag but also a larger wooden plank to make it’s way up the stairs and jumping in between levels without loosing it’s balance. The Atlas finished off with an incredible complex 540-degree, multi-axis flip.  Unlike Boston Dynamics’ four-legged Spot robot, Atlas is not commercially available. The technology team hopes to eventually give robots the technological capabilities to “perform real, physical demanding jobs with hustle”.  #atlas #robots #technews #bostondynamics
